#MEM id=dev source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/ENGINEERING-PRINCIPLES.md
M|dev|> Load this file before making any architecture dec, writing an API contract, or reviewing code.
M|dev|```
M|dev|Browser (React)
M|dev|↓
M|dev|Next.js API Routes (/app/api/*/route.ts)
M|dev|↓
M|dev|External Services (Anthropic | Apify | YouTube | GA4 | Supabase)
M|dev|```
M|dev|- API keys live only in Next.js API routes — never in client components.
M|dev|- Supabase `service_role` key used only server-side. Browser uses `anon` key via `createBrowserClient`.
M|dev|- Persistent data always in Supabase. `localStorage` only for ephemeral UI state (tab position, scroll).
M|dev|| Type | When to use | Rule |
M|dev||------|------------|------|
M|dev|| Server Component (default) | Data fetching, no user interaction | No `'use client'` directive |
M|dev|| Client Component | State, event handlers, browser APIs | Add `'use client'` at top of file only |
M|dev|| Route Handler | External API calls, DB writes | In `/app/api/*/route.ts` only |
M|dev|> `'use client'` boundary should be as deep in the component tree as possible. Never mark a layout or wrapper as client unless required.
M|dev|Dev writes contracts in Dev's mem.md before Raj implements. Every contract includes:
M|dev|```markdown
M|dev|**Request body:**
M|dev|```json
M|dev|{
M|dev|"ventureId": "string (required)",
M|dev|"fieldName": "string | number (required/optional)"
M|dev|}
M|dev|```
M|dev|**Success rsp (200):**
M|dev|```json
M|dev|{
M|dev|"fieldName": "value",
M|dev|"items": []
M|dev|}
M|dev|```
M|dev|**Error responses:**
M|dev|- `400` — Missing required field: `{ "error": "ventureId is required" }`
M|dev|- `404` — Resource not found: `{ "error": "vtr not found" }`
M|dev|- `500` — Internal error: `{ "error": "Failed to fetch data" }`
M|dev|**Notes:** [Any caching, rate limiting, or Vercel timeout considerations]
M|dev|```
M|dev|Raj implements to this exact shape. Mia builds components that consume this exact shape. No deviations without Dev ap.
M|dev|Dev checks every PR from Raj and Mia against this list:
M|dev|- [ ] Route validates required request fields before calling any external API
M|dev|- [ ] All external API calls are wrapped in try/catch with appropriate HTTP status codes
M|dev|- [ ] rsp shape exactly matches the contract in Dev's mem.md
M|dev|- [ ] No `any` type without a comment explaining why
M|dev|- [ ] API keys are read from `process.env` only — never hardcoded
M|dev|- [ ] `venture_id` is always included in Supabase writes
M|dev|- [ ] Apify: `CRON_SECRET` validated on cron routes via `Authorization: Bearer` header
M|dev|- [ ] No hardcoded color values — all colors use `var(--color-*)` tokens
M|dev|- [ ] `'use client'` only on components that genuinely need it
M|dev|- [ ] Every interactive element has ARIA attributes and keyboard nav
M|dev|- [ ] Loading state, error state, and empty state all handled
M|dev|- [ ] SSE consumption checks `event.data !== '[DONE]'` before `JSON.parse()`
M|dev|- [ ] No direct Supabase calls — data always fetched via API routes
M|dev|- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` passes with zero errors (Linux VM) / `npm run build` on Vercel/Windows
M|dev|- [ ] `npm run lint` passes with zero warnings
M|dev|- [ ] TypeScript strict — no `@ts-ignore` without explanation comment
M|dev|| Rule | Example |
M|dev||------|---------|
M|dev|| All request/rsp shapes in `lib/types.ts` | `import type { AgentConfig } from '@/lib/types'` |
M|dev|| No implicit `any` | `const data: unknown = await res.json()` then narrow |
M|dev|| Use `type` not `interface` for simple shapes | `type ApiResponse = { items: Item[] }` |
M|dev|| Discriminated unions for status types | `type Status = 'pending' \| 'done' \| 'error'` |
M|dev|| Explicit return types on exported functions | `export async function getVenture(): Promise<vtr>` |
M|dev|All AI streaming routes follow this pattern:
M|dev|```typescript
M|dev|export async function POST(req: Request) {
M|dev|const encoder = new TextEncoder()
M|dev|const stream = new ReadableStream({
M|dev|async start(controller) {
M|dev|try {
M|dev|const rsp = await anthropic.messages.stream({ ... })
M|dev|for await (const chunk of rsp) {
M|dev|if (chunk.type === 'content_block_delta') {
M|dev|controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(`data: ${chunk.delta.text}\n\n`))
M|dev|}
M|dev|}
M|dev|controller.enqueue(encoder.encode('data: [DONE]\n\n'))
M|dev|} catch (err) {
M|dev|controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(`data: [ERROR]\n\n`))
M|dev|} finally {
M|dev|controller.close()
M|dev|}
M|dev|}
M|dev|})
M|dev|return new rsp(stream, {
M|dev|headers: { 'cnt-Type': 'text/event-stream', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache' }
M|dev|})
M|dev|}
M|dev|```
M|dev|The `[DONE]` signal and try/catch inside the stream start are non-negotiable — Quinn checks for both.
M|dev|Before any deploy:
M|dev|- [ ] No `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in any file under `/app/**/page.tsx` or `/components/`
M|dev|- [ ] No `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` accessible in client bundle
M|dev|- [ ] Cron routes validate `Authorization: Bearer ${CRON_SECRET}` header
M|dev|- [ ] User-supplied `ventureId` values are validated against known ventures before use
M|dev|- [ ] No `eval()`, `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with unsanitized input, or SQL string concatenation
M|dev|Dev only approves merge when all of these are true:
M|dev|1. Quinn has issued ap verdict for the current phase
M|dev|2. `npm run build` passes (zero errors) in Quinn's ses
M|dev|3. `npm run lint` passes (zero warnings) in Quinn's ses
M|dev|4. All items in Dev's code rv checklist are satisfied
M|dev|5. Dev's mem.md has been updated with completion status
M|dev|No partial merges. The phase ships as a unit.
M|dev|- Milestone → tasks → owners → dependencies. Each task has exactly one owner.
M|dev|- Surface blockers and risks — not just the steps.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: plans without explicit owners or unresolved dependency chains.
M|dev|- Verify plan state before the first step. Check dependencies before starting each task.
M|dev|- Update the plan after each completed task — never let it go stale.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: marking a task complete without verifying its output.
M|dev|- Diverge → cluster → converge. Quantity before quality in the generation phase.
M|dev|- No criticism during diverge — every option gets written down first.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: evaluating approaches before the generation phase is complete.
M|dev|- Reproduce → isolate → hypothesize → test → doc. Never skip reproduce.
M|dev|- doc the root cause, not just the fix — future Dev will need to understand why.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: fixing symptoms without understanding what caused them.
M|dev|- Red → green → refactor. Write the failing test before the implementation.
M|dev|- Test behavior, not implementation detail. Each test has one assertion.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: tests that pass trivially or test internal state rather than external behavior.
M|dev|- ctx → what changed → what to focus on. Flag specific uncertainty areas explicitly.
M|dev|- Provide the PR link, relevant diff sections, and the acceptance criteria being met.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: PRs with no description — reviewers need ctx.
M|dev|- Respond to every comment. "Won't fix" requires an explanation, not silence.
M|dev|- Separate clarifying questions from disagreements — ask first, then decide.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: defensive responses; treat every comment as useful signal.
M|dev|- Build passes (`npm run build` zero errors). Lint passes (`npm run lint` zero warnings). Browser-verified for UI changes.
M|dev|- No feature ships without evidence of verification.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: marking done without running build and lint in the same ses.
M|dev|- Define agt role, input, output format, and handoff criteria before spawning.
M|dev|- Merge outputs before responding — never surface raw parallel agt output directly.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: dispatching with unresolved dependencies between workstreams.
M|dev|- One worktree per feature. Never commit directly to main from a worktree.
M|dev|- Clean up worktrees after the branch is merged.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: long-lived worktrees that drift far from the main branch.
M|dev|- Squash, rebase on main, PR title format: `type(scope): description`.
M|dev|- Delete the branch after merge. Update mem.md with completion status.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: merging without Quinn's ap verdict.
M|dev|- Define agt role + expected output format before spawning.
M|dev|- Verify subagent output before integrating — treat it as a PR, not a done deal.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: chaining subagent outputs without a verification step between them.
M|dev|- Server-side client with service role key for writes. RLS for user-scoped reads.
M|dev|- Index on frequently queried foreign keys. Prefer typed queries over raw SQL strings.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: exposing `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to client components.
M|dev|- Server Components by default. `'use client'` only when interactivity or browser APIs are required.
M|dev|- No secrets in client components — all external API calls go through `/app/api/` routes.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: unnecessary `useEffect` for data that can be fetched in a Server Component.
M|dev|- Parallel data fetching in Server Components. Streaming with `Suspense` for slow data.
M|dev|- Collocate data fetching with the component that uses it — don't prop-drill fetched data.
M|dev|- **Avoid**: request waterfalls in RSC trees; fetch all independent data in parallel.